                      <span>2000-05-01</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Having seen Hal Holbrook perform live in Mark Twain Tonight, I was delighted to aquire the DVD of his 1967 television broadcast performance.  I have long believed, and this DVD confirms  that Mark Twain Tonight is easily one of the greatest treasures of the American stage in the last half of the 20th Century.  That Mr. Holbrook has performed Mark Twain every year since 1954, in over 2000 shows, is  nothing short of miraculous.  This 90 minute performance brings the wisdom, humor and humanity of one of the most morally insightful men of the 19th century to life.  His words continue to be as hilarious, poignant and relevent in the 21st century as they were in his own time. </span>
                  
              
